
1. The Democratic Republic of the Congo is the second largest country in Africa and borders nine countries.
2. The people of the DRC represent over 200 ethnic groups, with nearly 250 languages and dialects spoken 
throughout the country.
3. Since the 1960s, the Congolese have endured over two decades of armed conflict with over 5.4 million people
 dead due to war-related causes, making it the deadliest conflict since World War II.
